ZH: 我们在写文章时可以用分号来分隔不同的句子。
EN: We can use a semicolon to separate different sentences when writing an essay.

ZH: 他先学了中文，然后分号学了法语。
EN: He learned Chinese first, and then he learned French.

ZH: 这个句子很长，最好使用分号将其分成两句。
EN: This sentence is very long, it would be better to use a semicolon to split it into two sentences.

ZH: 在列表中，用分号将不同的项分隔开。
EN: In a list, use semicolons to separate different items.

ZH: 我们需要在每个句子结束时使用分号。
EN: We need to use a semicolon at the end of each sentence.

ZH: 我今天要购买的东西有：苹果、橙子、香蕉；饼干、巧克力、糖果。
EN: The things I want to buy today are: apples, oranges, bananas; cookies, chocolates, candies.

ZH: 在正式的信件中，使用分号来分隔地址的行。
EN: In formal letters, use semicolons to separate lines of addresses.

ZH: 他对音乐很感兴趣，尤其喜欢古典乐；摄影也是他的爱好。
EN: He is very interested in music, especially classical music; photography is also his hobby.

ZH: 在这个长句子中，使用分号可以加强句子结构。
EN: In this long sentence, using a semicolon can enhance the sentence structure.

ZH: 请注意使用分号和冒号的区别。
EN: Please pay attention to the difference between semicolons and colons.

ZH: 妈妈说，如果我有问题可以随时给她发短信；她会帮助我解决。
EN: Mom said I can text her anytime if I have any questions; she will help me solve them.

ZH: 这封邮件需要分号来分隔收件人、抄送和密送。
EN: This email needs semicolons to separate recipients, carbon copies, and blind carbon copies.

ZH: 他的工作比较忙，每天都在开会；通常直到晚上才能回家。
EN: His work is quite busy, he has meetings every day; usually, he can't go home until the evening.

ZH: 分号在英语写作中可以用来表示因果关系。
EN: Semicolons can be used to indicate cause and effect relationships in English writing.

ZH: 约翰是个很有趣的人；他总是能说出迷人的故事。
EN: John is a very interesting person; he can always tell fascinating stories.

ZH: 她热爱运动；尤其是喜欢跑步和游泳。
EN: She loves sports; especially running and swimming.

ZH: 这部电影有各种不同的情节；它不仅有悬疑，还有浪漫和喜剧。
EN: This movie has various plots; it has not only suspense but also romance and comedy.

ZH: 分号可用于连接两个独立的句子。
EN: Semicolons can be used to connect two independent sentences.

ZH: 这篇文章的标题是：“大自然的美丽；山和海的魅力”。
EN: The title of this article is: "The Beauty of Nature; the Charms of Mountains and Seas".

ZH: 他足够努力，分号他的成绩一直很好。
EN: He works hard enough; hence, his grades have always been good.

ZH: 分号也可以用来分隔长数字。
EN: Semicolons can also be used to separate long numbers.
